en_407033_0	The Met Department announces that due to the low level atmospheric disturbance in the vicinity of Sri Lanka, prevailing showery condition is expected to continue over the island during next few days.
en_407033_1	Showers or thundershowers will occur in the most parts of the island after 2.00 p.m.Very heavy falls about 150 millimeter can be expected at some places in the North-western, North-Central, Central and Sabaragamuwa provinces.
en_407033_2	Heavy falls about 100 millimeter can be expected at some places elsewhere in the island.Showers or thundershowers may occur at several places in Western, Southern and Northern coastal areas in the morning too.Misty conditions can be expected at some places in the Western, Sabaragamuwa and Centralprovinces over the island during the morning.
en_407033_3	There may be temporary localized strong winds during thundershowers.
en_407033_4	General public is requested to take adequate precautions to minimize damages caused by lightning activity.
